    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200904/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-04"><time>2020-09-04</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Based on the novel In­con­solable Mem­o­ries by Cuban writer Ed­mundo Des­noes, the film is told through the lens of Ser­gio, an as­pir­ing wealthy bour­geois writer, in the af­ter­math of the 1961 Bay of Pigs In­va­sion. His fam­ily re­treats to Mi­ami as Cuba grap­ples with so­cial changes. The work is in­ter­spersed with real-life doc­u­men­tary footage of protests and po­lit­i­cal events. Part of the Non-Aligned Film Pro­gramme: Third Way/Af­ter Ban­dung, fea­tur­ing films that en­gage post-colo­nial pro­cesses cov­er­ing dif­fer­ent mo­ments and geopo­lit­i­cal con­texts. Hosted by</p>
    <p>NTU Centre for Con­tem­po­rary</p>
    <p>Art Sin­ga­pore.</p>
    <p>WHERE: The Sin­gle Screen, Block 43 Malan Road</p>
    <p>MRT: Labrador Park WHEN: Till Sun (noon & 1.45, 3.30 & 5.15pm) AD­MIS­SION: Free INFO: bit.ly/2QIs0cm</p>


